item.description: The Prairie Cardiac Foundation is happy to announce the new funding received in order to coordinate  the creation of a new protocol for patients suffering from AFIB.   Cardiologists from both Regina and Saskatoon will attend 3 meetings with the goal of having a single protocol for the province of Saskatchewan.
